## 4. Obligation Notices under the EU AI Act

> The following items are **legal obligations** of the deployer — not missing
> inputs. They cannot be added in the project settings; they must be implemented
> organisationally and evidenced. Violations can trigger fines of up to EUR 35 million
> or 7 % of global annual turnover (Art. 99 EU AI Act).

### ⚖️ Always apply (all deployers)

| Obligation | Legal basis | Evidenced by |
|---|---|---|
| Ensure AI literacy of staff (applies since {{ model.art4_effective_date | en_date }}) | Art. 4 EU AI Act | documented training/competence measures |

{% if model.bias_risk_annex_iii_nr_4 or (model.deployer_usecase and model.deployer_usecase.risk_level == "High") %}
### ⚖️ Due to high-risk classification (Annex III)

For high-risk AI, the following obligations must be established and documented before putting the system into service:

| Obligation | Legal basis | Evidenced by |
|---|---|---|
| FRIA — fundamental rights impact assessment before putting into service | Art. 27 EU AI Act | documented impact assessment |
| Conformity assessment (CE) by a notified body | Art. 43 EU AI Act | to be requested from the provider |
| Registration in the EU database | Art. 49 EU AI Act | before placing on the market |
| Human oversight (four-eyes principle, override capability) | Art. 14 EU AI Act | to be anchored organisationally |
| Automatic logging (audit trail, retention 5+ years) | Art. 12 EU AI Act | logging evidence |
{% endif %}

{% if model.risk_levels | selectattr("level", "equalto", "GPAI") | list %}
### ⚖️ Due to GPAI use

| Obligation | Legal basis | Evidenced by |
|---|---|---|
| Technical documentation, copyright policy, GPAI Code of Practice, transparency towards users | Art. 51–53 EU AI Act | published documentation + transparency disclosures |
{% endif %}

{% if model.bias_risk_annex_iii_nr_4 %}
### ⚖️ Due to use case: HR recruiting (Annex III No. 4 — Employment)

Automated applicant selection is a high-risk use case under EU AI Act Annex III No. 4.
Bias can lead to indirect discrimination (gender, age, origin, disability).
Legally relevant: Art. 22 GDPR (prohibition of purely automated decisions with legal
effect), AGG §§ 1–3 (German General Equal Treatment Act — protection against discrimination), Art. 10 EU AI Act (data quality for high-risk AI).

| Obligation | Legal basis | Evidenced by |
|---|---|---|
| Bias audit + four-eyes principle before every final selection decision | Annex III No. 4 · Art. 10 · Art. 14 EU AI Act | bias audit report + review protocols (see DPIA + ki_system_*.md) |
{% endif %}

